
Overview of noun bankruptcy

The noun bankruptcy has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                     
1. (1) bankruptcy -- (a state of complete lack of some abstract property; "spiritual bankruptcy"; "moral bankruptcy"; "intellectual bankruptcy")
2. (1) bankruptcy, failure -- (inability to discharge all your debts as they come due; "the company had to declare bankruptcy"; "fraudulent loans led to the failure of many banks")
3. bankruptcy -- (a legal process intended to insure equality among the creditors of a corporation declared to be insolvent)
